				<td colspan="2"><span>Hello everyone,
<br />

<br />
I'm new to the EQ scene but not new to being a bard. Been playing the class for eons on D&amp;D (yes the dice game) and on pc games so thought I'd give EQ a shot. 
<br />

<br />
Looks like there's lots to read and learn. I look forward to seeing how I can fare this time out.
<br />

<br />
I'm on the Tunare server and level 22 so far. Doing halfway decently I guess. Currently I've learned, ae kiting, chant kiting (just one chant so far) and looking forward to the other styles of solo and group play. 
<br />

<br />
I'm doing fairly I guess for being new. I've all my newly born quested bard armor (wood elf plate) and bought a wakazashi blade and walrus drum. So far that's about all I've done.
<br />

<br />
Being a veteran for many years in D&amp;D has nothing to do with this game I'm finding (or any other game for that matter). So I look forward to learning from you all. 
<br />

<br />
Give me a shout sometime if you're on Tunare or in general.
<br />

<br />
Cheers,
<br />

<br />
Riffz Old fart of a Scottish bard <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /> </span></td>
