			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: New to EQ<a name="60135"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Sep 2 04 11:01 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Which hand do you steer with?  This makes a HUGE difference in how you set up your keyboard.
<br />

<br />
I steer with my right hand on the arrow keys, and twist my hotkeys with my left hand on the number row.
<br />

<br />
Some folks use WASD for steering, and numpad or even mouse clicking for twisting.  (People who played a lot of first-person shooters like Quake are used to WASD steering and mouse twitching, hehe.)
<br />

<br />
Now, Cujo / Krescendo, a Bard I highly respect, mapped his casting to the F1 - F8 keys, and double taps them to twist.  (That is, you tap once to stop a song, then again to start a new one.  This is what you do on the number row if you use the song gems directly in the hotkey bank.)  The advantage to his setup, is that he has his entire hotkey bank for macros, clickies, and item swapping.  I tried this, but found that to reach the F-keys, my wrist could no longer rest on the desktop, and I couldn't stand it, lol.  In other words, my whole forearm had to be lifted off the desk to reach the keys, and I am accustomed to resting my whole forearm on the desk and still reaching the number row.
<br />

<br />
I'm sure this was MUCH more confusing than anything else you read so far, lmao.  Post how you steer, and I will see if I can help you figure out something that will work for you.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=564823">Scherzo Glissando </a><BR>
