				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: New to EQ<a name="60280"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Sep 3 04 3:30 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Klapton,
<br />

<br />
Well first off I'm older guy and have the reaction time of an elephant with a petrified trunk..but I digress. <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-13.gif" border="0" alt="LOL" hspace="2" />
<br />

<br />
Since I use a notebook there are no numpads to utilize. And just like you trying to 'twist' songs as you call it on the 1 - 10 or F1 - F8 keys makes me lift my hand too far. Tried that with lots of frustration. <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-7.gif" border="0" alt="Perplexed" hspace="2" />
<br />

<br />
So my setup is D,Z,C,V for movement. ASFG and WERT for songs to sing. Space is for jump and X is for ducking. As for switching instruments and weapons I'm horrid at it. I don't know how people can do that and fight and move and position all at once. 
<br />

<br />
I am good at using the F9 outside views and mouselook for AE kiting so far but that's about all. At level 23 I don't have those charm or chant songs yet to do the kiting I'm reading about yet.
<br />

<br />
Look good so far or am I daft and should stick to D&amp;D dice games? <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-2.gif" border="0" alt="Big Smile" hspace="2" /> 
<br />

<br />
Cheers,</span></td>
